\begin_layout Standard
(1
\begin_inset Formula $\implies$
\end_inset

3): Suppose 
\begin_inset Formula $(U,\phi)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $(V,\psi)$
\end_inset

 are charts on 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

 respectively such that 
\begin_inset Formula $U\cap F^{-1}(V)\neq\emptyset$
\end_inset

.
 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $p\in U\cap F^{-1}(V)$
\end_inset

.
 Then 
\begin_inset Formula $(U,\phi)$
\end_inset

 is a chart about 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $(V,\psi)$
\end_inset

 is a chart about 
\begin_inset Formula $F(p)$
\end_inset

.
 By 
\begin_inset ERT
