begin{example}
\backslash
label{example}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $X=\mathrm{Spec}\,A$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $X'=\mathrm{Spec}\,A'$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $A=\Bbbk[t]$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $A'=\Bbbk[t']$
\end_inset

.
 We glue the affine 
\begin_inset Formula $\Bbbk$
\end_inset

-schemes 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $X'$
\end_inset

 along open subsets as follows: let 
\begin_inset Formula $U=\mathrm{D}(t)$
\end_inset

, let 
\begin_inset Formula $U'=\mathrm{D}(t')$
\end_inset

, and let 
\begin_inset Formula $f\colon U'\to U$
\end_inset

 be the 
\begin_inset Formula $\Bbbk$
\end_inset

-scheme isomorphism corresponding to the 
\begin_inset Formula $\Bbbk$
\end_inset

-algebra isomorphism 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi\colon A_{t}\to A'_{t'}$
\end_inset

 defined by
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\varphi(t)=1/t'.
\]

\end_inset

Then the scheme obtained from this gluing datum is just 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{P}_{\Bbbk}^{1}$
\end_inset

.
 The closed points of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 are the points 
\begin_inset Formula $x=\langle\pi\rangle$
\end_inset

 corresponding to a monic irreducible 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi\in\Bbbk[t]$
\end_inset

.
 The residue field for 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 then is 
\begin_inset Formula $\kappa(x)=\Bbbk[t]\slash\pi$
\end_inset

 which is a finite extension of 
\begin_inset Formula $\Bbbk$
\end_inset

 of degree 
\begin_inset Formula $d=\deg\pi$
\end_inset

.
 The generic point of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 is the point 
\begin_inset Formula $\eta=\langle0\rangle$
\end_inset

 whose corresponding residue field is 
\begin_inset Formula $\kappa(\eta)=\Bbbk(t)$
\end_inset

 which is a transcendental extension of 
\begin_inset Formula $\Bbbk$
\end_inset

.
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi\neq t$
\end_inset

, then 
\begin_inset Formula $x\in U$
\end_inset

, and the point in 
\begin_inset Formula $X'$
\end_inset

 that 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 is glued to (via 
\begin_inset Formula $g$
\end_inset

) is the point 
\begin_inset Formula $x'=\langle\pi'\rangle$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi'=t^{d}\pi(1/t)$
\end_inset

.
 For instance, 
\begin_inset Formula $\langle t-\alpha\rangle$
\end_inset

 gets glued to 
\begin_inset Formula $(1-\alpha t'\rangle=\langle t'-\alpha^{-1}\rangle$
\end_inset

 for every 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha\in\Bbbk\backslash\{0\}$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{example}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

