begin{example}
\backslash
label{example}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 The morphism 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{C}[t,t^{-1}]\to\mathbb{C}[t,t^{-1},\varepsilon]\slash\langle\varepsilon^{n}-t\rangle$
\end_inset

 is etale and corresponds to a degree 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 covering space of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{G}_{m}\in\mathbf{Sch}\slash\mathbb{C}$
\end_inset

 with the group 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{Z}\slash n$
\end_inset

 of deck transformations.
 Indeed, this is because 
\begin_inset Formula $\partial_{\varepsilon}(\varepsilon^{n}-t)(e)=ne^{n-1}\neq0$
\end_inset

 for all nonzero 
\begin_inset Formula $e\in\mathbb{C}$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{example}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{example}
\backslash
label{example}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 be a ring, let 
\begin_inset Formula $t\in A$
\end_inset

, and let 
\begin_inset Formula $B=A_{t}$
\end_inset

.
 Furthermore set 
\begin_inset Formula $X=\mathrm{Spec}\,A$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Y=\mathrm{Spec}\,B$
\end_inset

.
 Then the morphism 
\begin_inset Formula $Y\to X$
\end_inset

 corresponding to the localization map 
\begin_inset Formula $A\to B$
\end_inset

 is etale.
 Indeed, it is locally of finite presentation since 
\begin_inset Formula $B=A[s]\slash\langle1-st\rangle$
\end_inset

.
 It is flat since localization is flat.
 Finally, 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega_{Y\slash X}^{1}=0$
\end_inset

 since this is true for Zariski open embeddings.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{example}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

