\]

\end_inset

and this is supported at 
\begin_inset Formula $t=0$
\end_inset

 (if 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathrm{char}\neq2$
\end_inset

).
 More generally suppose 
\begin_inset Formula $F\colon\mathbb{A}^{1}\to\mathbb{A}^{1}$
\end_inset

 is given by 
\begin_inset Formula $t\mapsto t^{p}$
\end_inset

 and furthermore assume that 
\begin_inset Formula $\Bbbk$
\end_inset

 has characteristic 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

.
 Then
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
